   398	def wire_client(iut: IutHandle) -> WireClient:
   399	    return WireClient(
   400	        base_url=iut.base_url,
   401	        experiment_id=iut.experiment_id,
   402	        extra_headers=iut.extra_headers,
   403	    )
   404	```
   405	
   406	The `WireClient` is a thin httpx wrapper that:
   407	
   408	- Talks raw HTTP/JSON, returning httpx `Response` objects (not decoded
   409	  models) so scenarios can assert on status codes, headers, and body.
   410	- Always sets `X-Eden-Experiment-Id` per chapter 07 §1.3 (the suite
   411	  tests the disagreement case explicitly by overriding it).
   412	- Adds `iut.extra_headers` to every request.
   413	- Does NOT retry, NOT decode problem+json into typed exceptions, NOT
   414	  paper over errors. All of those would mask the wire shape the
   415	  suite is verifying.
   416	
   417	### D. The reference IUT adapter
   418	
   419	In [`conformance/adapters/reference/adapter.py`](../../conformance/adapters/reference/adapter.py):
   420	
   421	```python
   422	import secrets
   423	import subprocess
   424	import sys
   425	import threading
   426	import time
   427	from pathlib import Path
   428	
   429	from conformance.harness.adapter import IutAdapter, IutHandle
   430	
   431	
   432	class ReferenceAdapter:
   433	    """Spawns a fresh task-store-server subprocess against in-memory storage."""
   434	
   435	    _PORT_ANNOUNCE_TIMEOUT = 15.0
   436	    _STOP_TIMEOUT = 5.0
   437	
   438	    def __init__(self) -> None:
   439	        self._proc: subprocess.Popen | None = None
   440	        self._stderr_buf: list[str] = []
   441	        self._stderr_thread: threading.Thread | None = None
   442	
   443	    def start(self, *, experiment_config_path: Path, experiment_id: str) -> IutHandle:
   444	        token = secrets.token_urlsafe(24)
   445	        self._proc = subprocess.Popen(
   446	            [
   447	                sys.executable, "-m", "eden_task_store_server",
   448	                "--store-url", ":memory:",
   449	                "--experiment-id", experiment_id,
   450	                "--experiment-config", str(experiment_config_path),
   451	                "--shared-token", token,
   452	                "--subscribe-timeout", "2.0",
   453	                "--port", "0",
   454	                "--host", "127.0.0.1",
   455	            ],
   456	            stdout=subprocess.PIPE,
   457	            stderr=subprocess.PIPE,
   458	            text=True,
   459	        )
   460	        port = self._read_port_announcement()
   461	        self._start_stderr_drain()
   462	        return IutHandle(
   463	            base_url=f"http://127.0.0.1:{port}",
   464	            experiment_id=experiment_id,
   465	            extra_headers={"Authorization": f"Bearer {token}"},
   466	        )
   467	
   468	    def stop(self) -> None:
   469	        if self._proc and self._proc.poll() is None:
   470	            self._proc.terminate()
   471	            try:
   472	                self._proc.wait(timeout=self._STOP_TIMEOUT)
   473	            except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:
   474	                self._proc.kill()
   475	                self._proc.wait(timeout=2.0)
   476	        # Drain stderr so the next scenario's pytest output isn't polluted.
   477	        if self._stderr_thread:
   478	            self._stderr_thread.join(timeout=1.0)
   479	```
   480	
   481	The `_read_port_announcement` helper duplicates the corresponding
   482	helper from
   483	[`reference/services/orchestrator/tests/test_e2e.py`](../../reference/services/orchestrator/tests/test_e2e.py)
   484	intentionally — copy is cheap, dependency from `conformance/` into
   485	`reference/services/orchestrator/tests/` is wrong direction.
   486	`conformance/` MUST NOT import from `reference/` outside
   487	`conformance/adapters/reference/`. CI gates this; see §H.
   488	
   489	The reference adapter takes a deliberate shortcut: `SqliteStore(":memory:")`
   490	rather than `PostgresStore`. Conformance does not test durability;
   491	[`reference/packages/eden-storage/tests/`](../../reference/packages/eden-storage/tests/)
   492	does. SQLite-in-memory gives the fastest possible test cycle.
   493	
   494	`--subscribe-timeout 2.0` is passed so the timeout-path subscribe test
   495	in §E.9 (`test_subscribe_empty_batch_after_timeout`) completes in 2-3
   496	seconds rather than the 30-second default. Chapter 07 §6.2 makes 30s
   497	a `RECOMMENDED:` value (i.e. SHOULD), so a 2-second window is
   498	spec-conforming. The reference-adapter-specific override is acceptable;
   499	a third-party adapter SHOULD pass an equivalently-short timeout for
   500	its own subject. The chapter-07 §6.2 conformance assertion in the
   501	test is "the subscribe response after timeout has the empty-batch
   502	shape," not "the timeout is 30 seconds."
   503	
   504	### E. Scenario inventory
   505	
   506	Every scenario's first docstring line cites the exact normative MUST
   507	it tests, in the format `spec/v0/<chapter>.md §<sec>`. The
   508	`tools/check_citations.py` helper (§I) walks every test and verifies
   509	the citation resolves. Any test whose citation cannot be verified is
   510	a CI failure.
   511	
   512	#### E.1 Task lifecycle (`test_task_lifecycle.py`)
   513	
   514	Each test creates a fresh `plan` task and exercises one transition.
   515	Tests assert both the post-condition (state machine) and the wire
   516	response (status + error type for negative cases).
   517	
   518	| Test | Asserts | Citation |
   519	|---|---|---|
   520	| `test_create_task_pending` | After `POST /tasks`, the task exists with `state == "pending"`, no `claim`. | 04 §2; 02 §3.1 |
   521	| `test_pending_to_claimed` | `POST /tasks/{T}/claim` returns 200 with claim object; subsequent read shows `state == "claimed"`. | 04 §1.2; §3.2 |
   522	| `test_claimed_to_submitted` | Submit with current token + plan payload returns 200; `state == "submitted"`. | 04 §4.1 |
   523	| `test_submitted_to_completed` | `POST /tasks/{T}/accept` returns 200; `state == "completed"`. | 04 §4.3 |
   524	| `test_submitted_to_failed_via_reject` | Reject with valid `reason` returns 200; `state == "failed"`. | 04 §4.3 |
   525	| `test_terminal_completed_rejects_writes` | After accept, every write op (claim, submit, accept, reject, reclaim) returns 409 `eden://error/illegal-transition`. | 04 §1.1, §4.4 |
   526	| `test_terminal_failed_rejects_writes` | Same for `failed`. | 04 §1.1 |
   527	| `test_pending_rejects_submit` | Submit on pending task returns 409 `illegal-transition`. | 04 §1.2 |
   528	| `test_pending_rejects_accept` | Accept on pending task returns 409. | 04 §1.2 |
   529	| `test_pending_rejects_reject` | Reject on pending task returns 409. | 04 §1.2 |
   530	| `test_claimed_rejects_accept` | Accept-without-submit returns 409. | 04 §1.2 |
   531	| `test_claim_rejected_when_not_pending` | Re-claim a `claimed` task returns 409. | 04 §3.4 |
   532	| `test_terminal_rejects_reclaim` | Reclaim of a `completed` or `failed` task returns 409. | 04 §5.1 |
