   534	#### E.2 Claim tokens (`test_claim_tokens.py`)
   535	
   536	| Test | Asserts | Citation |
   537	|---|---|---|
   538	| `test_token_present_on_claim` | Successful claim response carries `claim.token`. | 02 §3.4 |
   539	| `test_token_unique_across_tasks` | Two parallel claims on different tasks produce different tokens. | 04 §3.2 |
   540	| `test_token_unique_across_reclaim_cycles` | Reclaim → re-claim same task → token differs. | 04 §3.2; §5.2 |
   541	| `test_wrong_token_rejected` | Submit with a fabricated token returns 403 `eden://error/wrong-token`. | 04 §3.3 |
   542	| `test_token_invalidated_by_reclaim` | After operator reclaim, the prior token returns 403 wrong-token on submit. | 04 §5.2 |
   543	| `test_no_reclaim_while_claimed` | Second worker's claim against a claimed task returns 409 illegal-transition. | 04 §3.4 |
   544	
   545	The harness does NOT attempt to assert "tokens are unforgeable" — that
   546	is a SHOULD/MAY mechanism in chapter 04 §3.2. The MUST is uniqueness,
   547	which is testable.
