   647	
   648	| Test | Asserts | Citation |
   649	|---|---|---|
   650	| `test_implement_dispatch_atomic` | Creating an `implement` task: `task.created` AND `proposal.dispatched` both appear, and `read_proposal` shows `state == "dispatched"`. | 05 §2.2 |
   651	| `test_implement_terminal_completes_proposal` | Implementer task's `submitted → completed` transition: `task.completed` AND `proposal.completed` both appear; proposal is `state == "completed"`. | 05 §2.2 |
   652	| `test_implement_terminal_fails_proposal` | Implementer task's `submitted → failed`: `task.failed` AND `proposal.completed` both appear (proposal still goes to completed per chapter 4 §7; the proposal lifecycle ends regardless of task outcome). | 05 §2.2; 04 §7 |
   653	| `test_evaluate_terminal_success_emits_trial_succeeded` | Evaluate `submitted → completed` with worker `status=success`: `task.completed` AND `trial.succeeded` both appear; trial is `status == "success"`. | 05 §2.2; 04 §4.3 |
   654	| `test_evaluate_terminal_error_emits_trial_errored` | Evaluate `submitted → failed` with worker `status=error`: `task.failed` AND `trial.errored` both appear; trial is `status == "error"`. | 05 §2.2; 04 §4.3 |
   655	| `test_evaluate_terminal_eval_error_keeps_trial_starting` | Evaluate `submitted → failed` with worker `status=eval_error`: `task.failed` appears; trial stays `status == "starting"` (NO `trial.eval_errored` event yet — that fires only when the orchestrator decides to terminalize the trial). | 04 §4.3 |
   656	| `test_retry_exhausted_eval_error_terminalization` | After one or more `eval_error` cycles, an explicit `POST /trials/{T}/declare-eval-error` (the chapter 07 §4 endpoint binding the chapter 04 §4.3 retry-exhausted decision) atomically terminalizes the trial: trial.status flips `starting → eval_error` AND a `trial.eval_errored` event appears. (Codex review round 1 finding 2.) | 05 §2.2 retry-exhausted; 04 §4.3 |
   657	| `test_implement_reclaim_with_starting_trial` | Implement reclaim on a task whose execution had created a starting trial: `task.reclaimed` AND `trial.errored` both appear atomically. | 05 §2.2; 04 §5.4 |
